#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.75"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.75:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.75:0.2"
msgid "8. Yodhājīvavagga"
msgstr "8. Warriors"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: paṭhamayodhājīvūpamasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.75:0.3"
msgid "75. Paṭhamayodhājīvasutta"
msgstr "75. Warriors (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, yodhājīvā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, these five warriors are found in the world."

msgctxt "an5.75:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.75:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco yodhājīvo rajaggaññeva disvā saṃsīdati visīdati na "
"santhambhati na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, one warrior falters and founders at the mere sight of a cloud of "
"dust. He doesn’t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle."

#. VAR: Evarūpopi → evarūpo (bj)
msgctxt "an5.75:1.4"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti."
msgstr "Some warriors are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:1.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the first warrior found in the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ;"
msgstr "Furthermore, one warrior can prevail over a cloud of dust,"

msgctxt "an5.75:2.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho dhajaggaññeva disvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na "
"sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ."
msgstr ""
"but he falters and founders at the mere sight of a banner’s crest. He doesn’"
"t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle."

msgctxt "an5.75:2.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti."
msgstr "Some warriors are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:2.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the second warrior found in the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ sahati "
"dhajaggaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, one warrior can prevail over a cloud of dust and a banner’s "
"crest,"

#. VAR: ussāraṇaññeva → ussādanaṃ yeva (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.75:3.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho ussāraṇaññeva sutvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na "
"sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ."
msgstr ""
"but he falters and founders at the mere sound of turmoil. He doesn’t stay "
"firm, and fails to plunge into battle."

msgctxt "an5.75:3.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti."
msgstr "Some warriors are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:3.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the third warrior found in the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati "
"dhajaggaṃ, sahati ussāraṇaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, one warrior can prevail over a cloud of dust and a banner’s "
"crest and turmoil,"

#. VAR: haññati → āhaññati (bj)
msgctxt "an5.75:4.2"
msgid "api ca kho sampahāre haññati byāpajjati."
msgstr "but he’s killed or injured when blows are struck."

msgctxt "an5.75:4.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti."
msgstr "Some warriors are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:4.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the fourth warrior found in the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.90"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati "
"dhajaggaṃ, sahati ussāraṇaṃ, sahati sampahāraṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, one warrior can prevail over a cloud of dust and a banner’s "
"crest and turmoil and being struck."

msgctxt "an5.75:5.2"
msgid ""
"So taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā vijitasaṅgāmo tameva saṅgāmasīsaṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "He wins victory in battle, establishing himself as foremost in battle."

msgctxt "an5.75:5.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti."
msgstr "Some warriors are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:5.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is the fifth warrior found in the world."

msgctxt "an5.75:5.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca yodhājīvā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "These are the five warriors found in the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:6.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcime yodhājīvūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā "
"bhikkhūsu."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, these five people similar to warriors are found among the "
"monks."

msgctxt "an5.75:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

#. VAR: sandhāretuṃ → santānetuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.75:6.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rajaggaññeva disvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na "
"santhambhati, na sakkoti brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, one monk falters and founders at the mere sight of a cloud of dust. "
"He doesn’t stay firm, and fails to keep up the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.75:6.4"
msgid "Sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a "
"lesser life."

msgctxt "an5.75:6.5"
msgid "Kimassa rajaggasmiṃ?"
msgstr "What is his ‘cloud of dust’?"

msgctxt "an5.75:6.6"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu suṇāti:"
msgstr "It’s when a monk hears:"

msgctxt "an5.75:6.7"
msgid ""
"‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā kumārī vā abhirūpā dassanīyā "
"pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘In such and such a village or town there’s a women or a girl who is "
"attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty.’"

msgctxt "an5.75:6.8"
msgid ""
"So taṃ sutvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na sakkoti brahmacariyaṃ "
"sandhāretuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Hearing this, he falters and founders. He doesn’t stay firm, and fails to "
"keep up the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.75:6.9"
msgid "Sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a "
"lesser life."

msgctxt "an5.75:6.10"
msgid "Idamassa rajaggasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is his ‘cloud of dust’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo rajaggaññeva disvā saṃsīdati visīdati, "
"na santhambhati, na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who falters and founders at the "
"mere sight of a cloud of dust."

msgctxt "an5.75:7.2"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.75:7.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti."
msgstr "Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:7.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the first person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.91"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sahati rajaggaṃ;"
msgstr "Furthermore, one monk can prevail over a cloud of dust,"

msgctxt "an5.75:8.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho dhajaggaññeva disvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na "
"sakkoti brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ."
msgstr ""
"but at the mere sight of a banner’s crest he falters and founders. He doesn’"
"t stay firm, and fails to keep up the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.75:8.3"
msgid "Sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a "
"lesser life."

msgctxt "an5.75:8.4"
msgid "Kimassa dhajaggasmiṃ?"
msgstr "What is his ‘banner’s crest’?"

msgctxt "an5.75:8.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na heva kho suṇāti:"
msgstr "It’s when a monk doesn’t hear:"

msgctxt "an5.75:8.6"
msgid ""
"‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā kumārī vā abhirūpā dassanīyā "
"pāsādikā paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgatā’ti;"
msgstr ""
"‘In such and such a village or town there’s a women or a girl who is "
"attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty.’"

msgctxt "an5.75:8.7"
msgid ""
"api ca kho sāmaṃ passati itthiṃ vā kumāriṃ vā abhirūpaṃ dassanīyaṃ pāsādikaṃ "
"paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgataṃ."
msgstr ""
"But he sees for himself a women or a girl who is attractive, good-looking, "
"lovely, of surpassing beauty."

msgctxt "an5.75:8.8"
msgid ""
"So taṃ disvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na sakkoti brahmacariyaṃ "
"sandhāretuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Seeing her, he falters and founders. He doesn’t stay firm, and fails to keep "
"up the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.75:8.9"
msgid "Sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a "
"lesser life."

msgctxt "an5.75:8.10"
msgid "Idamassa dhajaggasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is his ‘banner’s crest’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:9.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who can prevail over a cloud of "
"dust,"

msgctxt "an5.75:9.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho dhajaggaññeva disvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na "
"sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ;"
msgstr "but he falters and founders at the mere sight of a banner’s crest."

msgctxt "an5.75:9.3"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.75:9.4"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti."
msgstr "Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:9.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the second person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:10.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati dhajaggaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, one monk can prevail over a cloud of dust and a banner’s crest,"

msgctxt "an5.75:10.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho ussāraṇaññeva sutvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na "
"sakkoti brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ."
msgstr ""
"but he falters and founders at the mere sound of turmoil. He doesn’t stay "
"firm, and fails to enter the battle."

msgctxt "an5.75:10.3"
msgid "Sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a "
"lesser life."

msgctxt "an5.75:10.4"
msgid "Kimassa ussāraṇāya?"
msgstr "What is his ‘turmoil’?"

#. VAR: ūhasati → ohasati (s1-3, km) | uhasati (mr)
#. VAR: ujjagghati → ujjhagghati (bj) | ujjhaggeti (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.75:10.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ araññagataṃ vā rukkhamūlagataṃ vā suññāgāragataṃ "
"vā mātugāmo upasaṅkamitvā ūhasati ullapati ujjagghati uppaṇḍeti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or "
"to an empty hut, when a female comes up to him. She smiles, chats, laughs, "
"and flirts with him."

#. VAR: ujjagghiyamāno → ujjhagghiyamāno (bj) | ujjhaggiyamāno (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.75:10.6"
msgid ""
"So mātugāmena ūhasiyamāno ullapiyamāno ujjagghiyamāno uppaṇḍiyamāno "
"saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na sakkoti brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ."
msgstr ""
"He falters and founders. He doesn’t stay firm, and fails to keep up the "
"spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.75:10.7"
msgid "Sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a "
"lesser life."

msgctxt "an5.75:10.8"
msgid "Idamassa ussāraṇāya."
msgstr "This is his ‘turmoil’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:11.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati dhajaggaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who can prevail over a cloud of "
"dust and a banner’s crest,"

msgctxt "an5.75:11.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho ussāraṇaññeva sutvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati, na "
"sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ;"
msgstr "but he falters and founders at the mere sound of turmoil."

msgctxt "an5.75:11.3"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.75:11.4"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti."
msgstr "Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:11.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the third person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.92"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:12.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati dhajaggaṃ, sahati "
"ussāraṇaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, one monk can prevail over a cloud of dust and a banner’s crest "
"and turmoil,"

msgctxt "an5.75:12.2"
msgid "api ca kho sampahāre haññati byāpajjati."
msgstr "but he’s killed or injured when blows are struck."

msgctxt "an5.75:12.3"
msgid "Kimassa sampahārasmiṃ?"
msgstr "What is his ‘blows are struck’?"

msgctxt "an5.75:12.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ araññagataṃ vā rukkhamūlagataṃ vā suññāgāragataṃ "
"vā mātugāmo upasaṅkamitvā abhinisīdati abhinipajjati ajjhottharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or "
"to an empty hut, when a female comes up to him. She sits right by him, lies "
"down, or embraces him."

msgctxt "an5.75:12.5"
msgid ""
"So mātugāmena abhinisīdiyamāno abhinipajjiyamāno ajjhotthariyamāno sikkhaṃ "
"apaccakkhāya dubbalyaṃ anāvikatvā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati."
msgstr ""
"Without rejecting the training and declaring his inability to continue, he "
"has sex."

msgctxt "an5.75:12.6"
msgid "Idamassa sampahārasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is his ‘blows are struck’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:13.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati dhajaggaṃ, "
"sahati ussāraṇaṃ, api ca kho sampahāre haññati byāpajjati;"
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who can prevail over a cloud of "
"dust and a banner’s crest and turmoil, but is killed or injured when blows "
"are struck."

msgctxt "an5.75:13.2"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.75:13.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti."
msgstr "Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:13.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the fourth person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:14.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati dhajaggaṃ, sahati "
"ussāraṇaṃ, sahati sampahāraṃ, so taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā vijitasaṅgāmo "
"tameva saṅgāmasīsaṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, one monk can prevail over a cloud of dust and a banner’s crest "
"and turmoil, and being struck. He wins victory in battle, establishing "
"himself as foremost in battle."

msgctxt "an5.75:14.2"
msgid "Kimassa saṅgāmavijayasmiṃ?"
msgstr "What is his ‘victory in battle’?"

msgctxt "an5.75:14.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ araññagataṃ vā rukkhamūlagataṃ vā suññāgāragataṃ "
"vā mātugāmo upasaṅkamitvā abhinisīdati abhinipajjati ajjhottharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or "
"to an empty hut, when a female comes up to him. She sits right by him, lies "
"down, or embraces him."

msgctxt "an5.75:14.4"
msgid ""
"So mātugāmena abhinisīdiyamāno abhinipajjiyamāno ajjhotthariyamāno "
"viniveṭhetvā vinimocetvā yena kāmaṃ pakkamati."
msgstr "But he disentangles and frees himself, and goes wherever he wants."

msgctxt "an5.75:14.5"
msgid ""
"So vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ "
"giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"He frequents a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a "
"ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of "
"straw."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.93"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:15.1"
msgid ""
"So araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ "
"ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"Gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, he sits "
"down cross-legged, with his body straight, and establishes his mindfulness "
"right there."

msgctxt "an5.75:15.2"
msgid ""
"So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ "
"parisodheti;"
msgstr ""
"Giving up desire for the world, he meditates with a heart rid of desire, "
"cleansing the mind of desire."

msgctxt "an5.75:15.3"
msgid ""
"byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī "
"byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti;"
msgstr ""
"Giving up ill will and malevolence, he meditates with a mind rid of ill "
"will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill "
"will."

msgctxt "an5.75:15.4"
msgid ""
"thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, "
"thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti;"
msgstr ""
"Giving up dullness and drowsiness, he meditates with a mind rid of dullness "
"and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of "
"dullness and drowsiness."

msgctxt "an5.75:15.5"
msgid ""
"uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, "
"uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti;"
msgstr ""
"Giving up restlessness and remorse, he meditates without restlessness, his "
"mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse."

msgctxt "an5.75:15.6"
msgid ""
"vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṅkathī kusalesu dhammesu, "
"vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up doubt, he meditates having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about "
"skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt."

msgctxt "an5.75:15.7"
msgid "So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
msgstr ""
"He gives up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. "

msgctxt "an5.75:15.8"
msgid "vivicceva kāmehi … pe … "
msgstr ""
"Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful "
"qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption … "

msgctxt "an5.75:15.9"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an5.75:16.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When his mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"he extends it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an5.75:16.2"
msgid ""
"So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ime āsavā’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"He truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’"
" … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads "
"to the cessation of suffering’. He truly understands: ‘These are defilements’"
" … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of "
"defilements’."

msgctxt "an5.75:16.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, "
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, his mind is freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "an5.75:16.4"
msgid "vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When it is freed, he knows it is freed."

msgctxt "an5.75:16.5"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"He understands: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’"

msgctxt "an5.75:16.6"
msgid "Idamassa saṅgāmavijayasmiṃ."
msgstr "This is his ‘victory in battle’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
#. VAR: ussāraṇaṃ → ussādanaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.75:17.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo sahati rajaggaṃ, sahati dhajaggaṃ, "
"sahati ussāraṇaṃ, sahati sampahāraṃ, so taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā "
"vijitasaṅgāmo tameva saṅgāmasīsaṃ ajjhāvasati;"
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who can prevail over a cloud of "
"dust and a banner’s crest and turmoil and being struck. He wins victory in "
"battle, establishing himself as foremost in battle."

msgctxt "an5.75:17.2"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.75:17.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti."
msgstr "Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.75:17.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the fifth person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

msgctxt "an5.75:17.5"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca yodhājīvūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā "
"bhikkhūsū”ti."
msgstr "These five people similar to warriors are found among the monks.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.75:17.6"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
